* v1.0.0
Tagger: Michael D Labriola <veggiemike@sourceruckus.org>
Date:   TBD

Pingenator v1.0.0

Finished off the last couple low-priority TODO items, and didn't come up with
anything else to add, leading us to an earlier than expected feature complete
1.0 release!

- Added type checking to IP address command line arguments.
- Defined minimum supported Pything version.
- Fixed truncated output when sending SIGINT to infinite ping (w/ -c0).

* v0.3.0
Tagger: Michael D Labriola <veggiemike@sourceruckus.org>
Date:   Mon Jan 31 15:17:02 EST 2022

Pingenator v0.3.0

Build system overhaul, including help2man generated manpage and dpkg target.

* v0.2.0
Tagger: Michael D Labriola <veggiemike@sourceruckus.org>
Date:   Tue Nov  9 11:19:29 EST 2021

Pingenator v0.2.0

Added sanity check to keep --count from turning into a fork bomb and fixed
problem where occasionally 2 responses get received when system is under load.

* v0.1.0
Tagger: Michael D Labriola <veggiemike@sourceruckus.org>
Date:   Sat Oct 23 13:14:02 EDT 2021

Pingenator v0.1.0

Initial release.  Everything seems to be workable.  There's still some cleanup
and minor tweaks to be made, but certainly good enough for an initial release.
